<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Chocolate Digestives has been named the nation's favourite biscuit in a new poll. </p>

<p>Some 2,000 Britons responded to the survey and declared the McVitie's classic their favourite biccie. </p>

<p>Shortbread came in second, with Chocolate Fingers, Jaffa Cakes and Chocolate Hobnobs making up the top five.  </p>

<p>The British are well-known for their love of a cup of tea and a biscuit or two to dunk into their brew. And now a new poll has ruled once and for all that the chocolate digestive (pictured) is the UK's best-loved biscuit, according to Perspectus Global</p>

